                            <comment id="13699987" author="ram_krish" created="Thu, 4 Jul 2013 10:42:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Viral&lt;br/&gt;
Are you planning to provide a patch? If not i can take this up?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13700064" author="jmspaggi" created="Thu, 4 Jul 2013 13:18:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This will also help to close &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7769&quot; title=&quot;Checksum and shortcurcuit status in UI&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-7769&quot;&gt;HBASE-7769&lt;/a&gt;... If we have the metric, we can display it in the UI, which will allow users to see if shortcircuit is used or not...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13700166" author="ram_krish" created="Thu, 4 Jul 2013 15:58:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can see that in the trunk version clicking on the HBase configuration link in the UI shows the list of configuration.  That would help us to know if the property is set or not set.&lt;br/&gt;
Anyway to address Virals&apos; concern we can expose a metric.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13700172" author="jmspaggi" created="Thu, 4 Jul 2013 16:02:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue with the properties, it&apos;s it&apos;s not because the property is there that it&apos;s used... something might avoid it to work well, there might be a typo, etc. So exposing the metric is better I think, then we can display this value in the UI and everyone will be happy &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13700176" author="ram_krish" created="Thu, 4 Jul 2013 16:10:58 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;something might avoid it to work well,&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ya i understand.  Will work for that. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13700220" author="ram_krish" created="Thu, 4 Jul 2013 17:04:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One problem here could be that since the shortcircuit read is done by the DFSClient on the HDFS side will we get some direct metrics on this? Let me see.&lt;br/&gt;
But if we want the checksum metrics that can be done because HBase explicitly switches to DFS checksum if its own checksum fails.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13700366" author="viralbajaria" created="Thu, 4 Jul 2013 22:39:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ram_krish&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ram_krish&quot;&gt;ramkrishna.s.vasudevan&lt;/a&gt; I haven&apos;t started working on it yet. If you have already done some investigation then feel free to take it up or else I can look into it. But as noted by you, DFSClient on the HDFS side should expose some metrics. I can&apos;t see it on the ganglia for dfs right now but I will ask on that list and see if we can get something to expose in the HBase UI.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13700446" author="ram_krish" created="Fri, 5 Jul 2013 04:00:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So i think we need HDFS to expose this metric wrt shortcircuit reads hit/miss count.&lt;br/&gt;
Checksum metrics are already getting covered in the metrics system.  So as Jean pointed out we can display the configuration and say whether it is turned on or not.&lt;br/&gt;
I think it should go in the RS metrics side because this configuration is of more importance when set in the RS side.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13700447" author="ram_krish" created="Fri, 5 Jul 2013 04:01:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can work on it Viral.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14330014" author="stack" created="Sat, 21 Feb 2015 05:53:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See related &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-9604&quot; title=&quot;Add metric on short-circuit reads&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-9604&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-9604&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
